    {
      "id": "efde6e4138435ae6679a0416a0275fb7b31b0de4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-12-24 09:22:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nIt seems that the writing client must return a non-zero blocks count to the OST for the glimpse AST reply. I think, but haven't checked, that the client normally returns lvb_blocks = 0 to the OST, in whig case it would be easy to just add the client block count to the server block count.\n\nIf the clients currently return a block count in the glimpse that was originally read from the OST, then the OST should only pass this on of the local block count is 0.\n\nThat will ensure that the block count returned to the client doing the stat will always be non-zero.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
